    "epsd_cover" is stored in the array "PodMetaContent": -> "epsd":
  </description>
  <chapter_context>
    Podcast Metadata
    Episode
  </chapter_context>
</US_DocBloc>

<US_DocBloc version="1.0" spok_lang="en" prog_lang="*">
  <slug>epsd_description</slug>
  <title>epsd_description</title>
  <description>
    The content-notification/content warnings for the episode.    
    Newlines are stored with a literal "\n". If "\n" is part of the text, it shall be escaped to "\\n"(see examples).
    
    It is meant to warn of potential harmful content, like suicide(see Werther-effect for more information), abuse, re-traumatizing content, etc
    
    Example:
      "epsd_description":"In this episode, we talk about the new Singelbert movies."
      
      "epsd_description":"In this episode, we talk about the new Singelbert movies.\nWe also talk about the implications of \\n in strings."
      
    "epsd_description" is stored in the array "PodMetaContent": -> "epsd":
  </description>
  <chapter_context>
    Podcast Metadata
    Episode
  </chapter_context>
</US_DocBloc>

